From: rfrankel@us.oracle.com (Rick Frankel)
Subject: Re: SLS flaming <yawn> !
Date: Mon, 25 Oct 1993 19:20:37 GMT

RE:
  SLS is still perceived as the "flagship" Linux distribution by many, probably
  because it has wider distribution than Slackware because it's been around

Not so. SLS is perceived as the flagship because all information in
the FAQ point the newbie to installing SLS. 

I am new to linux (2 mos), but an old unix hacker. When I got a
laptop specifically to run linux, I read the FAQ before downloading
anything else. EVERYTHING in the FAQ told be to get SLS. So, I got
SLS.

BTW, overall SLS has been fine for me. I've rebuilt the kernel a
couple of times (reduced configurations), and downloaded some updated
utils, but overall, it has worked aok.

To be fair, if I did it over again, I would do it from MCC, but only
because I want to build an environment where I know exactly what
utilites are installed, why and where.

rick

