From: tdunbar@vtaix.cc.vt.edu (Thomas Dunbar)
Subject: Re: TeX (xdvi) with SLS
Date: 26 Oct 1993 01:59:32 GMT

the standard xdvi includes the buttons unless one uses -Dexpert
 as the buttons take up space better used for text, i always define
them out. there are nice keyboard shortcuts, some of which 
are (see man page for more info):
    d: down
    u: up
    n: next page
    p: previous page
   s3: 1/3 scale (ie 100dpi
   s2: 1/2 scale
   g9: goto page 9
 

