>: I am running only one xterm (rxvt) and fvwm.
>: Is it because I am using slightly bigger font (should be 16 pt, or 18pt) ?
>
>: Please give me some suggestions.
>
>I began using X with a Ati graphics ultra card with the svga server using
>the Ati VGA part (this was on a 486/33 with 8 MB). This had a slow sreen
>output. When I exchanged the svga server into the the x8514scale server,
>which uses the accelerated 8514a part of the Ati card, my display became
>very fast. I do now have a second computer with linux. A 386DX-33 with
>8 MB RAM and a ET4000 card. This seems to have a much faster screen than
>my original setup with Ati VGA and the svga server.
>

One other thing you might look at.  The xterm program has a resource
that you can set for smooth or jump scrolling.  Smooth scrolling is
*much* slower.  To check, use the ctrl-MB2 to pull up the VT options
menu, and see if there is a check mark next to 'Enable Jump Scroll'.
If there is not, enable it and watch it fly (well, as much as xterm
can fly :-)
        I don't remember the resource off the top of my head, but you
should be able to set it in your .Xdefaults file.

